ğŸ“š Basic Usage
1ï¸âƒ£ Creating Arrays


import numpy as np

# 1D Array
arr = np.array([1, 2, 3, 4, 5])
print(arr)

# 2D Array
matrix = np.array([[1, 2, 3], [4, 5, 6]])
print(matrix)


2ï¸âƒ£ Array Operations

arr = np.array([1, 2, 3, 4, 5])

print(arr + 2)  # Add 2 to each element
print(arr * 3)  # Multiply each element by 3
print(np.sqrt(arr))  # Square root


3ï¸âƒ£ Special Arrays

np.zeros((3, 3))  # 3x3 array of zeros
np.ones((2, 2))  # 2x2 array of ones
np.eye(3)  # 3x3 Identity matrix
np.random.rand(4, 4)  # Random values


4ï¸âƒ£ Array Statistics

print(np.mean(arr))  # Mean
print(np.sum(arr))   # Sum
print(np.std(arr))   # Standard deviation

ğŸ¯ Conclusion
NumPy is a foundational library for data science, machine learning, and scientific computing. Mastering NumPy will help you work efficiently with numerical data in Python.

